quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,"And indeed, We had granted Abraham sound judgment early on, for We knew him well ňĻto be worthy of itňļ"
  21,52,"ňĻRememberňļ when he questioned his father and his people, ‚ÄúWhat are these statues to which you are so devoted?‚ÄĚ"
  21,53,"They replied, ‚ÄúWe found our forefathers worshipping them.‚ÄĚ"
  21,54,"He responded, ‚ÄúIndeed, you and your forefathers have been clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  21,55,"They asked, ‚ÄúHave you come to us with the truth, or is this a joke?‚ÄĚ"
  21,56,"He replied, ‚ÄúIn fact, your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, Who created them ňĻbothňļ. And to that I bear witness.‚ÄĚ"
  21,57,"ňĻThen he said to himself,ňļ ‚ÄúBy Allah! I will surely plot against your idols after you have turned your backs and gone away.‚ÄĚ"
  21,58,"So he smashed them into pieces, except the biggest of them, so they might turn to it ňĻfor answersňļ"
  21,59,"They protested, ‚ÄúWho dared do this to our gods? It must be an evildoer!‚ÄĚ"
  21,60,"Some said, ‚ÄúWe heard a young man, called Abraham, speaking ňĻillňļ of them.‚ÄĚ"
  21,61,"They demanded, ‚ÄúBring him before the eyes of the people, so that they may witness ňĻhis trialňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  21,62,"They asked, ‚ÄúWas it you who did this to our gods, O Abraham?‚ÄĚ"
  21,63,"He replied ňĻsarcasticallyňļ, ‚ÄúNo, this one‚ÄĒthe biggest of them‚ÄĒdid it! So ask them, if they can talk!‚ÄĚ"
  21,64,"So they came back to their senses, saying ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúYou yourselves are truly the wrongdoers!‚ÄĚ"
  21,65,"Then they ňĻquicklyňļ regressed to their ňĻoriginalňļ mind-set, ňĻarguing,ňļ ‚ÄúYou already know that those ňĻidolsňļ cannot talk.‚ÄĚ"
  21,66,"He rebuked ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúDo you then worship‚ÄĒinstead of Allah‚ÄĒwhat can neither benefit nor harm you in any way"
  21,67,Shame on you and whatever you worship instead of Allah! Do you not have any sense?‚ÄĚ
  21,68,"They concluded, ‚ÄúBurn him up to avenge your gods, if you must act.‚ÄĚ"
  21,69,"We ordered, ‚ÄúO fire! Be cool and safe for Abraham!‚ÄĚ"
  21,70,"They had sought to harm him, but We made them the worst losers"
  21,71,"Then We delivered him, along with Lot, to the land We had showered with blessings for all people"
  21,72,"And We blessed him with Isaac ňĻas a sonňļ and Jacob ňĻas a grandsonňļ, as an additional favour‚ÄĒmaking all of them righteous"
  21,73,"We ňĻalsoňļ made them leaders, guiding by Our command, and inspired them to do good deeds, establish prayer, and pay alms-tax. And they were devoted to Our worship"
  21,74,"And to Lot We gave wisdom and knowledge, and delivered him from the society engrossed in shameful practices. They were certainly an evil, rebellious people"
  21,75,"And We admitted him into Our mercy, ňĻforňļ he was truly one of the righteous"